songs.title: Reflection [FH4 Version]
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1: Dinah & Ally]
I must confess, you looking fresh (so fresh)
Yep I'm impressed, go 'head and flex (flex! turn up!)
Everybody be hating the way that you stealing the show
Cause ooh you be killing 'em just like little Terio
You can get, anything you want
And ain't nobody, ever telling you no
Don't need no filters on pictures before you post them on the 'gram
Shut down the internet, they don't even understand

[Pre-Chorus 1: Lauren]
Ooh, they don't make 'em quite like you
No ooh, it ain't bragging if you know it's true

[Chorus: Normani]
Oh where you from? Must be heaven
You'd be rich if looking good, is your profession
Think I'm love, cause you so sexy
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection

[Post-Chorus: Normani]
I'm talking to my own reflection, I'm talking to my own reflection
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection
I'm talking to my own reflection, I'm talking to my own reflection
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection

[Verse 2: Ally (Dinah)]
Why'd you think I'm putting on my favourite perfume?
Why'd you think this dress so tight that I can barely move?
Why'd you think I'm dancing in these uncomfortable shoes?
I did it all, I did it all, I did it all for you

[Pre-Chorus 2: Lauren & Dinah (Ally)]
Ooh, don't you ever get it confused
No, ooh, it ain't bragging if you know is true

[Chorus: Normani]
Oh where you from? Must be heaven
You'd be rich, if looking good, it's your profession
Think I'm love, cause you so sexy
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection

[Post-Chorus: Normani]
I'm talking to my own reflection, I'm talking to my own reflection
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection
I'm talking to my own reflection, I'm talking to my own reflection
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection

[Bridge: Ally]
Mirror, mirror on the wall, should I even return his call?
Mirror, mirror on the wall, should I even return his call?
Mirror, mirror on the wall, should I even return his call?
Mirror, mirror on the wall, on the, on the, on-on the wall

[Chorus: All]
Oh where you from? Must be heaven
You'd be rich, if looking good, is your profession
Think I'm love, cause you so sexy
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection

[Post-Chorus: Normani]
I'm talking to my own reflection, I'm talking to my own reflection
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection
I'm talking to my own reflection, I'm talking to my own reflection
Boy, I ain't talking about you, I'm talking to my own reflection
